        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New York</placeName>
                <date>14<hi rend="sup">th</hi> De 1856</date>.</p>
            <p>Dear Sir,</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">As I promised you to write<lb/> but did not find an opportunity
                before, I now take<lb/> my <sic>leasure</sic> to devote it to your
                correspondence.<lb/> I would furnish you with more good and far<lb/> more interested
                articles that the one I gave<lb/> you, but alas! Druble<add>?</add> for support do
                not<lb/> permit my mind to sit down and write<lb/> with a clear and correct
                attention, in the<lb/> first place, I am now out of business and<lb/> having no
                means for support so that I can<lb/> not sit down and write articles, but if
                wish<lb/> to have some and can make some allowance<lb/> I will furnish you as above.
                The article I gave<lb/> you, you can publish in your publication, but<lb/> for the
                next, after you communication I am willing<lb/> and will act. Please direct a note
                to, as below.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Your humble &amp; ob't sevt.</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">A. Henry Dreyer</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(9)"><placeName>35 Beckman Street</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)"><placeName>New York</placeName>.</p>
            <p><addressee>Rev Isaac Leeser</addressee>.</p>
            <p><placeName>Chestnut Street 371. Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
        </body>
    </text>
